Program: Outlook
Title: Something Doesn't Add Up
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04nqhh6
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 16 Jan 2017
When she was 19 years old, Axton Betz-Hamilton discovered that she had been a victim of identity theft. She vowed to track down the fraudster - and made a shocking discovery. In 2010 a bank error meant that Luke Moore was automatically granted any loan request he made. Over the next two years or so, he withdrew more than two million Australian dollars spending it all on sports cars, speed boats and memorabilia. Image: Fingerprint scan. Credit: Ian Waldie/Getty Images. Show less